{"TopicId":178827,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Space shuttle and iss","CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T03:32:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T03:32:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo i saw a video on the shuttle docking with the iss and then they open a hatch to get on the iss. Wheres that hatch and how did they get to it because you cant go through where it was docked right?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/KaX7DGSO31s?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T03:36:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a docking port inside the cargo bay immediately behind the crew cabin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy do you think they can\u0027t go through there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg/1200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022shuttle09.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022652\u0022 src=\u0022http://media.sacbee.com/static/weblogs/photos/images/july09/shuttle_sm/shuttle09.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022982\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-09T03:43:10Z\u0022 title=\u002210/09/2018 03:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Geonovast\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T03:54:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh okay that makes sense thank you! Im dumb lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223464652\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539056204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a docking port inside the cargo bay immediately behind the crew cabin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy do you think they can\u0027t go through there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg/1200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg/1200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media.sacbee.com/static/weblogs/photos/images/july09/shuttle_sm/shuttle09.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022shuttle09.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022652\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.sacbee.com/static/weblogs/photos/images/july09/shuttle_sm/shuttle09.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022982\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheres the thing theyre supposed to align with then when they dock to the shuttle?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerekL1963","CreatedById":57091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T04:21:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223464654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539057281\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192075\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jonda\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Jonda said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheres the thing theyre supposed to align with then when they dock to the shuttle?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlainly visible in both photographs.\u00A0 If you\u0027re asking \u0022where on the station?\u0022, I\u0027d have to ask you \u0022when?\u0022 because it moved about during various phases of station construction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T04:48:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs shown above, the docking port was behind the cockpit and also acted as an airlock for crew transfers. It was hollow, allowing crews to pass through. Much like the Apollo era docking ports which allowed crews to pass from the CSM to the LM.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tumblr_ns8fn9F85Q1qigaa4o1_1280.gif?w=60\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022285\u0022 src=\u0022https://i1.wp.com/68.media.tumblr.com/8ef1bd20abeb2033acd0728a2a30f16f/tumblr_ns8fn9F85Q1qigaa4o1_1280.gif?w=605\u0022 width=\u0022394\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223-8_m.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022379\u0022 src=\u0022https://history.nasa.gov/SP-4225/imagery/diagrams/shuttle/3-8_m.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough not clearly labeled, directly below the \u0027Mid Deck\u0027 label, is a split round shape, which is the airlock for the docking port in the cargo bay. They would open it when docked, then enter it, and go up (in reference to the shuttle\u0027s floor) into the ISS/Mir (seeing as those were it\u0027s only dockable destinations).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nibb31","CreatedById":7272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-09T07:16:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe docking modules were not originally part of the Shuttle design. They were built by Russia and retro-fitted as part of the Shuttle-Mir program. This is why the US segment of the ISS was fitted with Russian APAS docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, Columbia was never fitted with the docking equipment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerekL1963","CreatedById":57091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-10T05:40:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223464710\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539069392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00227272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nibb31\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, Nibb31 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is why the US segment of the ISS was fitted with Russian APAS docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe US modules are fitted with CBM.\u00A0 There are three PMA\u0027s (Pressurized Mating Adapter) that mount to CBM and provide APAS.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pressurized_Mating_Adapter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pressurized_Mating_Adapter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-10T09:14:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223464654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539057281\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192075\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jonda\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/9/2018 at 2:24 PM, Jonda said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh okay that makes sense thank you! Im dumb lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWheres the thing theyre supposed to align with then when they dock to the shuttle?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause APAS(and now the NASA docking system IDSS) isn\u0027t a probe drogue system you can have a docking target inside the docking ring.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/shuttle/sts-108/html/s108e5112.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/shuttle/sts-108/html/s108e5112.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-10T11:32:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome more images on APAS, maybe \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EActive docking ring deployed\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022640px-APAS-95_active_side.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/APAS-95_active_side.jpg/640px-APAS-95_active_side.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAfter capture but before retraction (on Mir)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022640px-STS-76_docking_with_MIR.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022417\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/STS-76_docking_with_MIR.jpg/640px-STS-76_docking_with_MIR.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EFully retracted and docked \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022684px-Orbiter_Docking_System_(STS-98).jp\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Orbiter_Docking_System_(STS-98).jpg/684px-Orbiter_Docking_System_(STS-98).jpg\u0022 width=\u0022684\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ENASA Docking System test (IDA/IDSS compatible) :\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NDS_docking_tests.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8b/NDS_docking_tests.gif\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-10T11:43:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah you can open the hatches and go through the thing. Fairly snug indeed - the opening is only 800 mm (80 cm, 0.8 m, 2\u0027 7.5\u0022) in diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T16:37:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223464652\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539056204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/8/2018 at 11:36 PM, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a docking port inside the cargo bay immediately behind the crew cabin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy do you think they can\u0027t go through there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg/1200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg/1200px-STS-115_Atlantis_docked.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media.sacbee.com/static/weblogs/photos/images/july09/shuttle_sm/shuttle09.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022shuttle09.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022652\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.sacbee.com/static/weblogs/photos/images/july09/shuttle_sm/shuttle09.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022982\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeautful!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-21T16:37:31Z\u0022 title=\u002210/21/2018 04:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Jonda\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}